") (wfw:commentRss nil "http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/simon-thomas-iwatch/feed/") (slash:comments nil "0"))) ("nvALT Update Rocks the New Simperium Sync" "<p>Over the weekend, Brett Terpstra update to nvALT to use the newer Simperium sync API, rather than Simplenote’s legacy syncing API. Which means nvALT syncing with Simplenote is now faster and more reliable.</p><p>In January, <a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/01/simplenote-alternatives/\">when I looked at Simplenote alternatives</a>, I mentioned a bug that existed when using nvALT and Simplenote syncing. In my testing so far with the newest version of nvALT, the previous bug appears to be squashed. New notes created in Simplenote, do not lose any data on their initial sync with nvALT. Brett Terpstra is my hero.</p><p><a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/nvalt-simperium-sync/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to 'nvALT Update Rocks the New Simperium Sync'\" class=\"glyph\">✚</a></p>" "http://brettterpstra.com/2013/03/24/nvalt-2-point-2-beta-104/" (20816 26316) new 16 nil nil ((title nil "nvALT Update Rocks the New Simperium Sync") (link nil "http://brettterpstra.com/2013/03/24/nvalt-2-point-2-beta-104/") (comments nil "http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/nvalt-simperium-sync/#comments") (pubDate nil "Mon, 25 Mar 2013 15:01:32 +0000") (dc:creator nil "Shawn Blanc") (category nil "Linked") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://shawnblanc.net/?p=11644") (description nil "Over the weekend, Brett Terpstra update to nvALT to use the newer Simperium sync API, rather than Simplenote&#8217;s legacy syncing API. Which means nvALT syncing with Simplenote is now faster and more reliable. In January, when I looked at Simplenote &#8230; <a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/nvalt-simperium-sync/\">(More)</a><a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/nvalt-simperium-sync/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to 'nvALT Update Rocks the New Simperium Sync'\" class=\"glyph\">✚</a>
") (content:encoded nil "<p>Over the weekend, Brett Terpstra update to nvALT to use the newer Simperium sync API, rather than Simplenote&#8217;s legacy syncing API. Which means nvALT syncing with Simplenote is now faster and more reliable.</p><p>In January, <a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/01/simplenote-alternatives/\">when I looked at Simplenote alternatives</a>, I mentioned a bug that existed when using nvALT and Simplenote syncing. In my testing so far with the newest version of nvALT, the previous bug appears to be squashed. New notes created in Simplenote, do not lose any data on their initial sync with nvALT. Brett Terpstra is my hero.</p><p><a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/nvalt-simperium-sync/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to 'nvALT Update Rocks the New Simperium Sync'\" class=\"glyph\">✚</a></p>
