") (wfw:commentRss nil "http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/twitter-rss-inboxes/feed/") (slash:comments nil "0"))) ("Reading into Google Reader’s Story" "<p>Khoi Vinh:</p><blockquote><p>There are some important takeaways from this unfortunate history. First in my mind is the fact that Google Reader didn’t beat every other feed reader purely because it was free. Google Reader won because it was an extremely well-executed example of interaction design.</p></blockquote><p><a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/reading-into-google-readers-story/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to 'Reading into Google Reader’s Story'\" class=\"glyph\">✚</a></p>" "http://www.subtraction.com/2013/03/18/reading-into-google-readers-story" (20811 30703) new 22 nil nil ((title nil "Reading into Google Reader’s Story") (link nil "http://www.subtraction.com/2013/03/18/reading-into-google-readers-story") (comments nil "http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/reading-into-google-readers-story/#comments") (pubDate nil "Thu, 21 Mar 2013 21:13:19 +0000") (dc:creator nil "Shawn Blanc") (category nil "Linked") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://shawnblanc.net/?p=11633") (description nil "Khoi Vinh: There are some important takeaways from this unfortunate history. First in my mind is the fact that Google Reader didn’t beat every other feed reader purely because it was free. Google Reader won because it was an extremely &#8230; <a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/reading-into-google-readers-story/\">(More)</a><a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/reading-into-google-readers-story/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to 'Reading into Google Reader’s Story'\" class=\"glyph\">✚</a>
