") (wfw:commentRss nil "http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/riposte-1-1/feed/") (slash:comments nil "0"))) ("MacStories’ Review of Alfred 2" "<p>Don Southard wrote an excellent review of <a href=\"http://www.alfredapp.com\">Alfred 2</a> which launched last Thursday. For the persnickety power-user there is only one way to navigate around a computer, and that is with the keyboard.</p><p>If you’re a current Alfred user, the upgrade to version 2 is a no brainer &mdash; it’s a massive update with some great new features and preferences that you are sure to benefit. As for me, I’ve been using Alfred 2 for a bit and I think it is a really amazing update. But in the end, I think I’m still a LaunchBar and Keyboard Maestro guy.</p><p>There are a lot of folks sharing the workflows they’ve built. You may want to check out <a href=\"http://alfred.daniel.sh\">Daniel Shannon’s list</a>, <a href=\"http://dferg.us\">David Ferguson’s site</a>, and, of course, the <a href=\"http://www.alfredforum.com/forum/3-share-your-workflows/\">Alfred Workflows forum</a>.</p><p><a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/southard-alfred-2-review/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to 'MacStories’ Review of Alfred 2'\" class=\"glyph\">✚</a></p>" "http://www.macstories.net/reviews/alfred-2-rewritten-from-the-ground-up-workflows-themes-and-more/" (20807 22655) new 29 nil nil ((title nil "MacStories’ Review of Alfred 2") (link nil "http://www.macstories.net/reviews/alfred-2-rewritten-from-the-ground-up-workflows-themes-and-more/") (comments nil "http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/southard-alfred-2-review/#comments") (pubDate nil "Mon, 18 Mar 2013 18:10:07 +0000") (dc:creator nil "Shawn Blanc") (category nil "Linked") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://shawnblanc.net/?p=11620") (description nil "Don Southard wrote an excellent review of Alfred 2 which launched last Thursday. For the persnickety power-user there is only one way to navigate around a computer, and that is with the keyboard. If you&#8217;re a current Alfred user, the &#8230; <a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/southard-alfred-2-review/\">(More)</a><a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/southard-alfred-2-review/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to 'MacStories&#8217; Review of Alfred 2'\" class=\"glyph\">✚</a>
") (content:encoded nil "<p>Don Southard wrote an excellent review of <a href=\"http://www.alfredapp.com\">Alfred 2</a> which launched last Thursday. For the persnickety power-user there is only one way to navigate around a computer, and that is with the keyboard.</p><p>If you&#8217;re a current Alfred user, the upgrade to version 2 is a no brainer &mdash; it&#8217;s a massive update with some great new features and preferences that you are sure to benefit. As for me, I&#8217;ve been using Alfred 2 for a bit and I think it is a really amazing update. But in the end, I think I&#8217;m still a LaunchBar and Keyboard Maestro guy.</p><p>There are a lot of folks sharing the workflows they&#8217;ve built. You may want to check out <a href=\"http://alfred.daniel.sh\">Daniel Shannon&#8217;s list</a>, <a href=\"http://dferg.us\">David Ferguson&#8217;s site</a>, and, of course, the <a href=\"http://www.alfredforum.com/forum/3-share-your-workflows/\">Alfred Workflows forum</a>.</p><p><a href=\"http://shawnblanc.net/2013/03/southard-alfred-2-review/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to 'MacStories&#8217; Review of Alfred 2'\" class=\"glyph\">✚</a></p>
